To change the theme of Zsh to 'agnoster' in Oh My Zsh, follow these steps:
1. Set `ZSH_THEME="agnoster"` in your `~/.zshrc` to enable the theme.
2. Install one of the patched fonts from Vim-Powerline (https://github.com/powerline/fonts) or patch your own (https://github.com/powerline/fontpatcher) for the special characters.
3. Optionally, set `DEFAULT_USER` to your regular username to hide the 'user@hostname' information when you're logged in as yourself on your local machine.
4. Alternatively, add `prompt_context(){}` to `~/.zshrc` to always hide the 'user@hostname' information.
Dependencies include Powerline Fonts: https://github.com/powerline/fonts and Nerd Fonts: https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts. 
Note: The theme requires Powerline or Nerd fonts for special characters.
